			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>MetaEdit+ for Collaborative Language Engineering and Language Use (Tool Demo)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JuhaPekkaTolvanen.html">Juha-Pekka Tolvanen</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997379">10.1145/2997364.2997379</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> MetaEdit+ is a language workbench, and the paper demonstrates collaborative features in that tool.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagL">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> It discusses collaboration support for maintaining and evolving languages and the models built with them.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagL">T6B: Industrial</span></a><ul><li> The demo is grounded in industrial-style collaboration needs and practical experiences.
</li></ul></li></ul>
